- admin: red
- field_user: green
- viewer: gray

Test Steps:
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/auth/login \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  -d 'username=admin&password=admin123'

Test Steps:

2. curl -X GET http://localhost:8000/api/auth/me \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer {token}'
Expected Result: Returns user object with username/email/role/permissions

Test Steps:
curl -X GET http://localhost:8000/api/auth/me \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer invalid_token'
Expected Result: Returns 401 Unauthorized error

Test Description: Test listing users with admin role

Test Steps:

Test Description: Verify network map displays after login
Test Steps:
1. Login as any user
2. Navigate to map view
3. Observe map display
Expected Result: Map shows poles/connections/conductors for KET site

Test Description: Test network API calls include auth token
Test Steps:
1. Login and open DevTools Network tab
2. Load network data
3. Check request headers
Expected Result: All API calls include Authorization: Bearer header

Test Steps:
1. Login as any user
2. Click Export to Excel
3. Download file
Expected Result: Excel file downloads successfully

1. Login as admin
2. Navigate to upload view
3. Select Excel file
4. Upload file
Expected Result: File uploads and processes successfully
